// Level 3: Compound Conditions Test
// Success Criteria: 60%+ correct execution with compound contexts
//
// Task: Learn that action depends on BOTH conditions being true
// Pattern 1: (red & bright) → ^left → G
// Pattern 2: (blue & bright) → ^right → G
//
// This tests context sensitivity with multiple simultaneous inputs

*volume=100
*setopname 1 ^left
*setopname 2 ^right

// === LEARNING PHASE ===

// Teach Pattern 1: (red & bright) → ^left → G
red. :|:
bright. :|:
5
^left. :|:
10
<goal --> achieved>. :|:
100

// Teach Pattern 2: (blue & bright) → ^right → G
blue. :|:
bright. :|:
5
^right. :|:
10
<goal --> achieved>. :|:
100

// === TESTING PHASE ===

// Test 1: red & bright → should trigger ^left
red. :|:
bright. :|:
2
<goal --> achieved>! :|:
1

// Wait
100

// Test 2: blue & bright → should trigger ^right
blue. :|:
bright. :|:
2
<goal --> achieved>! :|:
1

// Wait
100

// Test 3: red alone (no bright) → should NOT execute (or random)
red. :|:
2
<goal --> achieved>! :|:
1

// Wait
100

// Test 4: red & bright again → should trigger ^left
red. :|:
bright. :|:
2
<goal --> achieved>! :|:
1
